'''飲料'''是供[[人類|人類]]飲用的[[液體|液體]]。除了解渴的基本功能外，飲料在人類文化中也扮演著重要的角色。常見的飲料類型包括[[咖啡|咖啡]]、[[手搖飲|手搖飲]]、[[茶|茶]] 等，但不包括水。

==歷史==
[[水|水]]是世界上消耗最多的飲料<ref name="Griffiths">{{cite book|last=Griffiths|first=John|title=Tea: The Drink That Changed the World|url=https://archive.org/details/teadrinkthatchan0000grif|publisher=Andre Deutsch|year=2007|isbn=978-0-233-00212-5}}</ref>，然而地球上97%的水是不可飲用的鹽水<ref name="USGS dist">{{cite web|url=http://ga.water.usgs.gov/edu/waterdistribution.html|title=Earth's water distribution|publisher=United States Geological Survey|access-date=2009-05-13|archive-date=2012-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120629055146/http://ga.water.usgs.gov/edu/waterdistribution.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。[[淡水|淡水]]存在於河流、湖泊、濕地、地下水和冰凍的冰川中<ref>[http://ga.water.usgs.gov/edu/earthwherewater.html Where is Earth's water?] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214091601/http://ga.water.usgs.gov/edu/earthwherewater.html |date=2013-12-14 }}, [[United_States_Geological_Survey|United States Geological Survey]].</ref>。地球上只有不到1%的淡水供應可以通過具有成本效益的地表水和地下水源獲得<ref>{{cite book|last=Van Ginkel|first=J. A.|title=Human Development and the Environment: Challenges for the United Nations in the New Millennium|publisher=United Nations University Press|year=2002|pages=198–199|isbn=978-92-808-1069-1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uvv89FTDlboC|access-date=2022-03-28|archive-date=2020-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302135725/https://books.google.com/books?id=uvv89FTDlboC|dead-url=no}}</ref>。當人體脫水時，人就會感到口渴，這種對液體的渴望導致本能地需要喝水，口渴由下丘腦調節，以響應身體電解質水平的細微變化，以及血液循環量的變化，完全不喝水會比去除氧氣以外的任何其他物質更快地導致死亡<ref name="Cheney">{{cite journal|last=Cheney|first=Ralph|date=July 1947|title=The Biology and Economics of the Beverage Industry|journal=Economic Botany|volume=1|issue=3|pages=243–275|jstor=4251857|doi=10.1007/bf02858570|s2cid=20752304}}</ref>。在西方文化中，水通常是冷喝的。在中國文化中，它通常是熱飲<ref>{{cite news|last1=Liu|first1=Nicole|title=China's go-to beverage? Hot water. Really.|url=http://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-china-hot-water-20160313-story.html|access-date=2016-03-14|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|date=2016-03-12|archive-date=2022-03-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328183414/https://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-china-hot-water-20160313-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[牛奶|牛奶]]被視為“原始”飲料之一<ref>{{cite journal|last=Richards|first=Edgar|date=1890-09-05|title=Beverages|journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]]|publisher=American Association for the Advancement of Science|volume=16|issue=396|pages=127–131|jstor=1766104|doi=10.1126/science.ns-16.396.127|pmid=17782638|bibcode=1890Sci....16..127R|url=https://zenodo.org/record/1448319|access-date=2022-03-28|archive-date=2022-03-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328183442/https://zenodo.org/record/1448319|dead-url=no}}</ref>，水和牛奶在歷史上一直是基本飲料<ref name="Cheney"/>。隨著社會的發展，人們發現了從不同地區的植物中提取酒精飲料的技術，迄今為止發現的最早的葡萄酒生產考古證據是在格魯吉亞（約公元前 6000年）和伊朗（約公元前 5000年）的遺址<ref name=independent8k>{{cite news |first=David |last=Keys |title=Now that's what you call a real vintage: professor unearths 8,000-year-old wine |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/now-thats-what-you-call-a-real-vintage-professor-unearths-8000yearold-wine-84179.html |work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]] |date=2003-12-28 |access-date=2011-03-20 |archive-date=2015-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925153329/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/now-thats-what-you-call-a-real-vintage-professor-unearths-8000yearold-wine-84179.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Cultures of The World Georgia">{{cite book |title=Cultures of The World Georgia|last1=Spilling |first1=Michael |last2=Wong |first2=Winnie |year=2008 |isbn=978-0-7614-3033-9 |page=128 }}</ref><ref name=indie>{{cite news|first=Amy|last=Ellsworth|title=7,000 Year-old Wine Jar|url=http://www.penn.museum/blog/collection/125th-anniversary-object-of-the-day/7000-year-old-wine-jar-object-of-the-day-24/|date=2012-07-18|accessdate=2022-03-28|archive-date=2012-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120826123906/http://www.penn.museum/blog/collection/125th-anniversary-object-of-the-day/7000-year-old-wine-jar-object-of-the-day-24/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，早在公元前3000年新石器時代的歐洲就可能已經知道啤酒<ref>[http://www.stonepages.com/news/archives/000123.html] {{Wayback|url=http://www.stonepages.com/news/archives/000123.html |date=20170712080128 }} ''Prehistoric brewing: the true story'', 22 October 2001, Archaeo News. Retrieved 13 September 2008</ref>。茶可能起源於中國雲南，在商代開始作為藥用飲料<ref name="storyoftea">{{cite book|author1=Mary Lou Heiss|author2=Robert J. Heiss|title=The Story of Tea: A Cultural History and Drinking Guide|url=https://archive.org/details/storyofteacultur0000heis}}</ref>。第一種巧克力飲料被認為是大約2,500-3,000年前由瑪雅人創造的，而可可飲料是公元1400 年阿茲特克文化的重要組成部分<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/foodanddrink/6194447/Aztecs-and-cacao-the-bittersweet-past-of-chocolate.html|work=Telegraph|title=Aztecs and cacao: the bittersweet past of chocolate|author=Bee Wilson|date=2009-09-15|accessdate=2022-03-28|archive-date=2014-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418180336/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/foodanddrink/6194447/Aztecs-and-cacao-the-bittersweet-past-of-chocolate.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Trivedi">{{cite magazine|last1=Trivedi|first1=Bijal|title=Ancient Chocolate Found in Maya "Teapot"|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2002/07/0717_020717_TVchocolate.html|magazine=National Geographic|access-date=2017-07-15|date=2012-07-17|archive-date=2017-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630094718/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2002/07/0717_020717_TVchocolate.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。咖啡種植首先出現在阿拉伯南部，飲用咖啡的最早可信證據出現在15世紀中葉也門的蘇菲派聖地<ref name="Wein34">{{cite book |last1=Weinberg |first1=Bennett Alan |last2=Bealer |first2=Bonnie K. |title=The World of Caffeine: The Science and Culture of the World's Most Popular Drug |year=2001 |isbn=978-0-415-92722-2 |publisher=Routledge |location=New York |url=https://archive.org/details/worldofcaffeines00benn |access-date=2015-11-18|pages=[https://archive.org/details/worldofcaffeines00benn/page/n380 3]–4}}</ref>，可能在17世紀的文藝復興時期進入歐洲社會<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|last=Outram|first=Dorinda|title=The Enlightenment|url=https://archive.org/details/enlightenment00outr|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1995}}</ref>。第一種市售的人工碳酸飲料據信是由 Thomas Henry 在1770年代後期生產的<ref>{{cite book|last=Steen|first=Dr. David|author2=Ashhurst, Philip.|title=Carbonated Soft Drinks: Formulation and Manufacture|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2008|pages=1–2|isbn=978-1-4051-7170-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LfphGPaZtzwC|access-date=2022-03-28|archive-date=2021-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211118073518/https://books.google.com/books?id=LfphGPaZtzwC|dead-url=no}}</ref>，消費量最大的碳酸軟飲料由三大全球品牌生產：可口可樂、百事可樂和 Dr Pepper Snapple 集團<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reportlinker.com/ci02018/Soft-Drink.html|title=Soft Drink Industry: Market Research Reports, Statistics and Analysis|publisher=Report Linker|access-date=2013-06-10|archive-date=2022-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220218030438/https://www.reportlinker.com/ci02018/Soft-Drink.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==生產==
水是所有飲料的主要成分，也是大多數飲料的主要成分。水在飲用前經過淨化，包括過濾和添加化學品，例如氯化。世界衛生組織強調了純淨水的重要性，他們指出94%的腹瀉死亡（每年180萬人，是全球感染性死亡的第三大原因）可以通過改善受害者生活環境的質量來預防，特別是安全的水<ref>{{cite book |url=https://www.who.int/water_sanitation_health/publications/combating_diseasepart1lowres.pdf |publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]] |title=Combating Waterborne Diseases at the Household Level |page=11 |year=2007 |isbn=978-92-4-159522-3 |access-date=2022-03-28 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308084514/http://www.who.int/water_sanitation_health/publications/combating_diseasepart1lowres.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[巴氏殺菌|巴氏殺菌]]是將液體在指定溫度下加熱一段時間，然後立即冷卻的過程。該過程減少了液體中微生物的生長，從而延遲了變質的時間。它主要用於牛奶，在巴氏殺菌之前牛奶通常會感染病原菌，因此比發達國家普通飲食的任何其他部分更容易引起疾病<ref name=wilson>{{Citation | last = Wilson | first = G. S. | title = The Pasteurization of Milk | journal = British Medical Journal | volume = 1 | issue = 4286 | year = 1943 | pages = 261–262 | pmc=2282302 | pmid=20784713 | doi=10.1136/bmj.1.4286.261}}</ref>。

[[發酵|發酵]]是將糖轉化為乙醇的代謝過程，自新石器時代以來人類就使用發酵來生產飲料，在釀酒過程中葡萄汁與酵母在厭氧環境中混合以進行發酵<ref name="cox">Jeff Cox ''"From Vines to Wines: The Complete Guide to Growing Grapes and Making Your Own Wine"'' pgs 133–136 Storey Publishing 1999 {{ISBN|1-58017-105-2}}</ref>。葡萄酒中的糖分含量和發酵時間決定了葡萄酒的酒精度和甜度<ref name="Bird">D. Bird ''"Understanding Wine Technology"'' pg 67–73 DBQA Publishing 2005 {{ISBN|1-891267-91-4}}</ref>。

含有兩種或兩種以上成分的酒精混合飲料稱為雞尾酒，雞尾酒最初是烈酒、糖、水的混合物<ref>{{cite book|title=How To Mix Drinks|url=https://archive.org/details/howtomixdrinkso00schugoog|author=Thomas, Jerry|year=1862|publisher=Dick & Fitzgerald}}</ref>，這個詞現在經常用於幾乎所有含有酒精的混合飲料，包括混合飲料、混合飲料等<ref name=Regan>{{cite book|title=The Joy of Mixology|url=https://archive.org/details/joyofmixology0000rega|author=Regan, Gary|year=2003|publisher=Potter}}</ref>。今天的雞尾酒通常包含一種或多種烈酒和一種或多種混合飲料，例如蘇打水或果汁，其他成分可能是糖、蜂蜜、牛奶、奶油和各種草藥<ref>{{cite book|title=The Craft of the Cocktail|author=DeGroff, Dale|year=2002|publisher=Potter}}</ref>。可樂、橙子、各種植物根、生薑和檸檬通常用於製作不含酒精的碳酸飲料<ref name="SIVASANKAR">{{cite book|last=Sivasankar|first=B.|title=FOOD PROCESSING AND PRESERVATION|publisher=PHI Learning Pvt. Ltd.|year=2002|pages=314|chapter=24|isbn=978-81-203-2086-4|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tbxGHBUY0BcC|access-date=2022-03-28|archive-date=2022-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220311065837/https://books.google.com/books?id=tbxGHBUY0BcC|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==種類==
[[咖啡|咖啡]]呈微酸性（pH 5.0–5.1）<ref>[http://www.thecoffeefaq.com/7health.html#coffeeacidic Coffee and Health] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thecoffeefaq.com/7health.html#coffeeacidic |date=20160823160650 }}. Thecoffeefaq.com (2005-02-16). Retrieved on 2013-01-22.</ref>，其含有咖啡因，對人體有刺激作用，是世界上最受歡迎的飲料之一<ref name="Villanueva">{{cite journal |doi=10.1002/ijc.21587 |title=Total and specific fluid consumption as determinants of bladder cancer risk |year=2006 |last1=Villanueva |first1=Cristina M. |last2=Cantor |first2=Kenneth P. |last3=King |first3=Will D. |last4=Jaakkola |first4=Jouni J.K. |last5=Cordier |first5=Sylvaine |last6=Lynch |first6=Charles F. |last7=Porru |first7=Stefano |last8=Kogevinas |first8=Manolis |journal=International Journal of Cancer |volume=118 |issue=8 |pages=2040–7 |pmid=16284957|s2cid=27175168 |doi-access=free }}</ref>。咖啡對人類健康的影響一直是許多研究的主題。然而，就咖啡的相對益處而言，結果有所不同<ref>{{cite book |last=Kummer |first=Corby |date=2003-08-19 |title=The Joy of Coffee: The Essential guide to Buying, Brewing, and Enjoying |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qNLrJqgfg7wC |publisher=Houghton Mifflin |location=Boston |isbn=978-0-618-30240-6 |access-date=2022-03-28 |archive-date=2022-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328203157/https://books.google.com/books?id=qNLrJqgfg7wC |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

熱巧克力，也稱為飲用巧克力或可可，是一種加熱飲料，由融化的巧克力或可可粉、加熱的牛奶或水以及通常的甜味劑組成，熱巧克力上面可以加生奶油。用融化的巧克力製成的熱巧克力有時被稱為飲用巧克力，其特點是甜度較低，稠度較高<ref>{{Cite book|title=Chocolate: history, culture, and heritage |last1=Grivetti |first1=Louis E. |first2=Howard-Yana |last2=Shapiro  |year=2009 |publisher=John Wiley and Sons |isbn=978-0-470-12165-8 |page=345 }}</ref>。

茶是世界上消費量第二大的飲料，它是通過在沸水中浸泡茶樹灌木的干葉製成的<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DJ2j_bX6WTUC|title=Tea: The Drink that Changed the World|author=Martin, Laura C.|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|year=2007|pages=7–8|ref=Martin|isbn=978-0-8048-3724-8|access-date=2022-03-28|archive-date=2022-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111102756/https://books.google.com/books?id=DJ2j_bX6WTUC|dead-url=no}}</ref>。茶葉可以以不同的方式加工，從而產生外觀和味道不同的飲料：中國黃茶、綠茶經過蒸、烤、曬；烏龍茶是半氧化的，看起來是綠黑的；紅茶是完全氧化的<ref>{{cite book|last=Gibson|first=E.L.|author2=Rycroft, J.A.|others=Watson, R.; Martin, C.|title=Psychological and Physiological Consequences of Drinking Tea ''in Handbook of Behavior, Food and Nutrition''|editor=Victor R. Preedy|publisher=Springer|year=2011|pages=621–623|chapter=41|isbn=978-0-387-92271-3|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KuAEPOPbW6MC|access-date=2022-03-28|archive-date=2022-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128115259/https://books.google.com/books?id=KuAEPOPbW6MC|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

